<br>
I guess what I meant was that after the first cast, the mana you saved would apply to the next casting and there by lessen your medding time by 5%.<br>
<br>
The way that you put it is much clearer, though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
An other thing that most people fail to take into accounts is the fact that focus effect of different types will stack together. <br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
I snagged the following from Casters' Realm: <br>
<br>
Can you explain how the overlapping Focus items will stack, particularly with mana reduction items?<br>
<br>
When casting a spell, you get the benefit of the best focus item of a given type. If you cast a DoT spell and were wearing a Mana Preservation item (-10% mana cost) and an Affliction Efficency item (-25% mana cost), you would use the Affliction Efficiency item bonus.<br>
<br>
If you had on the same gear and you cast a direct damage spell, it would use the Mana Preservation item bonus instead, since Affliction Efficiency only works with DoTs. <br>
<br>
Focus effects of different types will work together however. If you have on a mana saving item, a spell haste item, and a duration extending item, all three of these can work on the same spell. It's only items of the same focus type that don't stack. <br>
<br>
- Rich<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
This fact is very important and of great benefits to everyone. Let's take a  quick look at it. Take Mana Preservation + Improved Healing... Up to 10 and 20 percent respectively. In use, they stack! <br>
<br>
You are saving up to 10% in mana per cast, for up to 20% more healing...<br>
<br>
Umm, Umm, need I say more? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
How about this: Mana Preservation + Improved Healing + Spell Haste = for an effective mana saving of up to 30% in up to 15% less casting time?<br>
<br>
Mana Preservation + Extended Enhancement + Enchancement Haste + Extended Range = up to 10% mana saving + a fix 15% duration increase for buffs + up to 30% less casting time + with an increase of up to 15% in casting range...<br>
<br>
Say after me: ME LIKE ME LIKE ME LIKE. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
